metadata.name: Copenhagen Interpretation #57
metadata.description:
The Copenhagen Interpretation of quantum physics suggests that objects don't have physical properties until being observed.

In this generative piece by itsgalo and Sp√∏gelsesmaskinen, a set of objects are being held in "superposition" and finally positioned when observed and minted.

Use mouse/touch to zoom, pan, and rotate. Press 's' to grab a screenshot. Best viewed in Firefox.

metadata.name: those rainy days #9
metadata.description:
endless loop.

instructions:

press 'r' to start and stop rain sound ( works in fullscreen mode ).
tap anywhere to freeze and unfreeze animations.
mouse interacts with camera perspective.

note: all shapes are generative and code based. there are a couple image textures that I created  for this piece, to "dirty" certain elements, but there are no pre-created objects, shapes or layouts. It is all generated when minting.
 
please be patient as it takes a few seconds to load. thank you for your understanding.

metadata.name: Constructions #23
metadata.description:
At the beginning, a program is generated from various commands. Further, the agent, following this program, forms a certain structure, which can be seen in the picture.

Controls:
spacebar - pause / continue
s - download .png
c - clear image
t - speed up / slow down the animation

Add &scale=N to the end of the URL, replacing N with the desired number of pixels to get the image at the desired resolution.

metadata.name: Urban Inception Redux #149
metadata.description:
Urban Inception Redux borrows from the original Circle City project and goes bigger, 6x bigger to be exact, and adds a whole new alternate reality, more rings, and a new skew potential. 

PLEASE BE PATIENT - This project has a lot of computations and may take a minute or two to render. 

This project creates a 12 layer composition that can be exported as an SVG and plotted or used to cut a physical out of wood or acrylic using a laser. With each layer being a single contiguous element. 

More info about the project and physicals can be found at: 
https://alleditions.art/p/urban-inception-redux

Shift P - Export a PNG
Shift S - Export an SVG
Shift E - explode the layers

metadata.name: Maale-Witz #5
metadata.description:
What lies unseen beneath the black ?

‚ÄúMaale-Witz‚Äù by Antti Pussinen is a boolean conceptual generative NFT painting. 

With colourful brush strokes, a painting is created. The algorithmic artist ponders for a bit and decides to take a more conceptual approach: The painting is painted over with black. What was before, still exist, but invisible.  


‚ÄúMaale-Witz‚Äù offers the viewer two options: either keep the expressionistic painting by clicking on the image within 4 seconds after painting has been finished or see the colours disappear giving the viewer the conceptual black square. 



Features:
Number of brush strokes [90,120,150,180,210,240,270,300]
Colour spectrum width [Monochrome(4.9%),Narrow(27%),Mid(23%),Wide(32%,Very Wide(11,1%)

A visual only feature: If some colour remains visible from under the edge of black, the artwork can be considered rare.

Test outputs can be seen at 
www.twitter.com/antti_pussinen/status/1460906974657318912

metadata.name: Impending Cloths #81
metadata.description:
IC makes use of fabric's potential for contrasts.
The same piece of cloth can seem to be falling, perfectly still and ready to be blown away, all at the same time.
It can look "very digital" while also achieving a high degree of texture. And so on, and so forth. Contrast and potential.
Also, "h" can be pressed to download in high resolution, although it may take up to a minute.

metadata.name: RGB Elementary Cellular Automaton #61
metadata.description:
Stephen Wolfram's Elementary Cellular Automaton where 3 different rules are drawn in the Red, Green and Blue color components of the image.

Rules are selected randomly among a pre-selection of 53 rules from which nice behaviors emerge.

Tokens can have a cell size in the [1; 20] range.
